/-!
# Spinor.SpinorTenfoldCliffordGroup

The algebraic (even) Clifford group acting on the Fock spinor model: the
group-level entry point of the `Spin(10)` stabilizer program.

## Design decision: algebraic GSpin, no analysis

The group-level statements of `Sources/Spin10_stabilizer.txt` (Lemma S1
transitivity, Lemma S2 stabilizer, the Selector Theorem) need a concrete
group acting on the trusted Fock model `PhysicsSM.Spinor.SpinorTenfoldFock`.
We deliberately avoid Lie-group analysis (exponentials, connectedness):
instead, the group is generated **algebraically** by the invertible Clifford
operators of *anisotropic* vectors.

- For `v : V10` with `Q10 v ŌēĀ 0` the Clifford operator `gammaEnd v` is a
  unit: the Clifford square relation
  `cliffordAction v (cliffordAction v psi) = Q10 v ŌĆó psi`
  (trusted, `PhysicsSM.Spinor.SpinorTenfoldCAR`) gives the explicit inverse
  `(Q10 v)Ōü╗┬╣ ŌĆó gammaEnd v`.
- `evenCliffordGroup` is the subgroup of `(Module.End Ōäé FockSpinor)╦Ż`
  generated by **products of two** such units. This is the standard
  algebraic model of the even Clifford group `GSpin(10, Ōäé)` in its spinor
  representation: even products preserve chirality, conjugation on the
  `gammaEnd` image is by (twisted) reflections, and over `Ōäé` the
  Cartan-Dieudonne theorem makes these products cover the full special
  orthogonal action on `V10`.

`evenCliffordGroup` contains every nonzero scalar `c ŌĆó 1` (see
`scalarUnit`): it is `GSpin`, not `Spin`. This is intentional - marked
transitivity statements ("`g` carries `psi` to `phi` exactly, not just
projectively") are *cleaner* with the scalars available, and the eventual
restriction to `Spin(10)` (spinor norm 1) can be cut out later via the main
anti-involution, which on this concrete model is the adjoint with respect
to the Chevalley pairing of `PhysicsSM.Spinor.SpinorTenfoldPurity`. Until
that refinement lands, theorems proved here are about `GSpin(10, Ōäé)` and
must not be advertised as `Spin(10)` statements.

## Main declarations

- `gammaEnd` : the Clifford action as a linear endomorphism (`Module.End`).
- `gammaUnit` : the Clifford operator of an anisotropic vector, as a unit.
- `evenCliffordGroup` : the subgroup generated by pair products of units.
- `flipVec`, `flipUnit`, `flipSet` : the hyperbolic mode-flip vectors
  `e_i + f_i` (with `Q10 = 1`), their units, and the index bookkeeping.
- `scalarUnit` : every nonzero scalar `c ŌĆó 1` realized inside
  `evenCliffordGroup` (as `gammaUnit (c ŌĆó flipVec 0) * gammaUnit (flipVec 0)`).
- `reflectTwist` : the twisted reflection
  `u Ōå” (B10 u v / Q10 v) ŌĆó v - u`, which is what conjugation by a single
  `gammaUnit v` induces on the `gammaEnd` image (proved in the trusted
  module `PhysicsSM.Spinor.SpinorTenfoldCliffordConj`).
- `PreservesChirality` : the chirality-preservation predicate for
  endomorphisms.

## Successor modules (trusted core)

- `PhysicsSM.Spinor.SpinorTenfoldCliffordConj` : conjugation =
  twisted reflection, B10/Q10 invariance, chirality preservation of the
  even group, injectivity of `gammaEnd`.
- `PhysicsSM.Spinor.SpinorTenfoldBasisOrbit` : mode-flip action on
  basis spinors and marked transitivity of `evenCliffordGroup` on the even
  wedge-monomial basis (the normal-form core of Lemma S1).

## Conventions

Everything follows the trusted Fock conventions of
`PhysicsSM.Spinor.SpinorTenfoldFock`: hyperbolic split `V10 = W ŌŖĢ W*`,
`Q10 (a, b) = ╬ŻßĄó aßĄó bßĄó`, `B10 v w = ╬ŻßĄó (vŌéüßĄó wŌééßĄó + vŌééßĄó wŌéüßĄó)`, so
`B10 v v = 2 * Q10 v`. The Clifford square is `Q10`-normalized (not
`B10`-normalized): `gammaEnd v * gammaEnd v = Q10 v ŌĆó 1`.

## Sources

- C. Chevalley, "The Algebraic Theory of Spinors and Clifford Algebras"
  (Clifford group, twisted conjugation).
- Internal research notes: `Sources/Spin10_stabilizer.txt`.
- Provenance: clean-room formalization; no external code copied.

Status: trusted - no `s o r r y`.
-/

